Definition: a bond that is issued at a deep discount from its value at maturity and pays no interest during the life of the bond
Example: the commonest form of zero-coupon security
Synonyms: zero-coupon_bond, zero-coupon_security, bond, noun, group, corporation, c, act, government, a, that, is, issued, at, deep, discount, from, its, value, maturity, and, pays, no, interest, during, the, life, of, commonest, form, zero-coupon, security
Category: noun.possession
